# VaultWares — AI Assistant Instructions (Tier 1)
This file is intentionally short. It points to the canonical protocol table of contents.
## Always do this first (routines)
1) Open: `C:\Users\Administrator\Desktop\Github Repos\vaultwares-docs\instructions\ROUTER.md`
2) Execute the routines section (always).
3) Scan all protocol categories, select the relevant ones, then read only the selected summaries in category order.
4) Read full notes only when the user explicitly says: `read full notes`
## Immutable company rules (summary pointers)
- Privacy first, security in service of privacy, then functionality/performance/scalability/devex.
- User-facing strings must exist in English (EN) and Quebec French (QC); plan for QC text being 15-20% longer.
- For UI/branding: use VaultWares design tokens; never hardcode colors/fonts/spacing. Start at `vaultwares-themes/AGENTS.md`.
- For networking/ops: tailnet-first, SSH tailnet-only. Start at `instructions/summaries/NETWORK_INFRASTRUCTURE.md`.
## Mandatory agent ledger (last step before replying)
Run:
`& "C:\Users\Administrator\Desktop\Github Repos\agent-ledger\scripts\record-agent-change.ps1" -Project "<name>" -Kind "<kind>" -Summary "<summary>" -Commands @("<cmd>") -Files @("<file>")`
If you cannot access the ledger repo, say so in the reply and include a compact ledger block for later capture.
